Reasoning: The paper discusses fundamental aspects of cellular automata, including dynamics, topological, and algebraic aspects, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of Discrete Structures (cs.DS). The paper also touches on information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY) through its discussion of strictly temporally periodic points. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the subfields of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) due to its exploration of algorithmic and complexity issues in cellular automata.
